## Feature Color Assignments

Each AI feature has a dedicated color ramp used consistently across: popover button, badge, history entry icon, and highlight overlay.

| Feature | Ramp | Badge bg | Badge text | History icon bg | PDF highlight |
|---------|------|----------|------------|-----------------|---------------|
| Note | Vanilla Custard | 50 | 800 | 100 | **500** (bright yellow — PDF only) |
| Translate | Honeydew | 50 | 800 | 100 | — |
| Summarize | Frosted Mint | 50 | 800 | 100 | — |
| Chat | Powder Blue | 50 | 800 | 100 | — |

**Rule:** Vanilla Custard 500 (`#ffee00`) is reserved exclusively for PDF text highlight overlays. Never use it as a UI fill anywhere else. Use 50 or 100 for all UI badge/chip backgrounds.

---

## Typography

Font family: system-ui / sans-serif (Tailwind default). Only two font weights are used: **400** (regular) and **500** (medium). Never use 600 or 700 — they feel heavy against this palette.

| Role | Size | Weight | Notes |
|------|------|--------|-------|
| Page title | 22px | 500 | |
| Section heading | 18px | 500 | |
| Card / item title | 15px | 500 | |
| Body | 14px | 400 | Line height 1.7 |
| Caption / metadata | 12px | 400 | Page numbers, timestamps, file size |
| Section label | 11px | 500 | Uppercase, 0.07em letter-spacing |

Sentence case everywhere. Never title case or all-caps (except the 11px section label).

No mid-sentence bold. Code identifiers go in `code` style, not **bold**.

